WEBVTT

00:05.000 --> 00:12.000
Good afternoon. I am Oleg Levitsky, a professor at the Russian Economic Academy.

00:12.000 --> 00:19.000
At the Academy, I teach MBA courses, human resources management, management of organizations, and sociology.

00:19.000 --> 00:26.000
I am also an active HR consultant and advise many foreign and domestic companies.

00:27.000 --> 00:35.000
The topic of our meeting today is the analysis of the variety of approaches that exist in foreign and Russian companies,

00:35.000 --> 00:41.000
which change their sphere of activity, which change their functioning.

00:41.000 --> 00:45.000
That is, the whole complex of the sphere of problems is associated with changes in the company,

00:45.000 --> 00:51.000
with changes in the team in the company, with changes in the interaction of the management system.

00:57.000 --> 01:05.000
Of course, the first question that arises in this regard is what we will understand under the organizational changes.

01:05.000 --> 01:13.000
It should be said that despite the fact that the problem of change is a traditional problem of management

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
and has been analyzed and studied for about a century and a half,

01:17.000 --> 01:21.000
nevertheless, there is a common opinion and a common approach to what change is,

01:22.000 --> 01:28.000
what are its qualitative characteristics, what quantitative aspects are associated with it, still does not exist.

01:28.000 --> 01:34.000
We, of course, will not go into theoretical debate about what organizational changes are,

01:34.000 --> 01:41.000
but will pay attention to those significant characteristics that, if necessary, have practical significance

01:41.000 --> 01:49.000
and indicate that the company has somehow changed, changed its sphere of activity,

01:49.000 --> 01:54.000
changed its method of work, changed its methodology of providing services,

01:54.000 --> 01:58.000
methodology of positioning on the market, changed its brand.

01:58.000 --> 02:03.000
When we talk about organizational development, about organizational changes,

02:03.000 --> 02:09.000
then usually we understand a certain normative strategy of retraining.

02:09.000 --> 02:16.000
There is a company, there are employees of this company, there is a certain product that this company produces

02:16.000 --> 02:20.000
and provides for the market, which is its competitive advantage,

02:20.000 --> 02:24.000
which is the niche that the company occupies on the market.

02:24.000 --> 02:28.000
Naturally, since the events that take place on the market,

02:28.000 --> 02:34.000
since the demands of consumers, the needs of consumers, the psychology of consumers are constantly changing,

02:34.000 --> 02:42.000
then in this regard, if the company wants to constantly be in the framework of economic development,

02:42.000 --> 02:47.000
it must react to these changes, it must join the feedback that exists,

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
and, accordingly, it must change if necessary.

02:51.000 --> 02:56.000
If the company, no matter how successful it is, stops changing,

02:56.000 --> 02:59.000
then there is a period of stagnation, a period of stagnation,

02:59.000 --> 03:07.000
which will inevitably end with the company losing its position and generally ceasing to exist.

03:07.000 --> 03:11.000
The corresponding examples are all what we will look at next.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.000
So, when we talk about organizational development,

03:14.000 --> 03:18.000
we mean, first of all, the presence of a retraining strategy.

03:18.000 --> 03:22.000
Organizational development is not a 7-minute process.

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
That is, someone wanted to change something, and we make changes.

03:26.000 --> 03:31.000
If we are talking about organization and organizational development,

03:31.000 --> 03:35.000
then, first of all, there is a certain planned strategy,

03:35.000 --> 03:38.000
when there is a goal that needs to be achieved,

03:38.000 --> 03:42.000
when there are ways to achieve this goal,

03:42.000 --> 03:50.000
when there is a business plan, a business planning that concerns the processes that will be associated with the changes,

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
when certain funds are invested,

03:54.000 --> 03:58.000
when significant effort is invested to make these changes happen,

03:58.000 --> 04:06.000
and, accordingly, we must always know at the very beginning what we want to get in the end.

04:06.000 --> 04:12.000
Only in this case can we say that organizational development will be purposeful, not accidental.

04:12.000 --> 04:18.000
If we know what the changes are for and for what purpose,

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
both inside and within the operating company.

04:20.000 --> 04:26.000
As for the retraining strategy, the development strategy,

04:27.000 --> 04:36.000
it is primarily aimed at changing beliefs, assessments and attitudes to work.

04:36.000 --> 04:42.000
For these are the main subjective factors that are largely central

04:42.000 --> 04:46.000
in terms of obtaining the desired result,

04:46.000 --> 04:49.000
in terms of positioning the company in the market,

04:49.000 --> 04:55.000
in terms of obtaining the desired business results, the desired commercial success.

04:55.000 --> 05:01.000
In addition to the retraining strategy, aimed at changing beliefs, assessments and attitudes to work,

05:01.000 --> 05:07.000
the central issue of organizational development is the problem of adaptation.

05:07.000 --> 05:12.000
Adaptation to the changes that occur on the part of the market,

05:12.000 --> 05:15.000
that occur on the part of the consumer-oriented companies.

05:15.000 --> 05:20.000
If a company wants to meet the requirements,

05:20.000 --> 05:24.000
if it wants to make a profit,

05:24.000 --> 05:29.000
it must react very clearly and very subtly

05:29.000 --> 05:34.000
and adapt to the changes that occur in the environment.

05:34.000 --> 05:39.000
And it is the reaction to these changes that is, in fact, the main,

05:39.000 --> 05:45.000
the main driving factor, the very motivation that is aimed at organizational development

05:45.000 --> 05:49.000
for obtaining the final result, for obtaining the final goal.

05:49.000 --> 05:54.000
It should be said that organizational development is a process that has its own structure,

05:54.000 --> 05:57.000
which has its own systematization.

05:57.000 --> 06:04.000
In this sense, all organizational development includes a certain organizational reconstruction.

06:04.000 --> 06:09.000
There is one regular schedule, there is one regular structural division.

06:10.000 --> 06:16.000
And if organizational development occurs, it can change as a company structure,

06:16.000 --> 06:20.000
it can change as a system of duties, as a system of relationships,

06:20.000 --> 06:23.000
as a system of any approaches that exist in the company.

06:23.000 --> 06:29.000
And this is the reconstruction of the already existing system.

06:29.000 --> 06:32.000
The existing system can be very successful.

06:32.000 --> 06:38.000
But, nevertheless, this system cannot be unchanged,

06:38.000 --> 06:43.000
at least simply because the external situation changes,

06:43.000 --> 06:47.000
the internal situation, the situation in the company changes,

06:47.000 --> 06:53.000
new people appear, new employees appear, new owners appear, new shareholders appear.

06:53.000 --> 07:00.000
And, of course, all these changes, which are a complex process,

07:00.000 --> 07:03.000
must be taken into account.

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
In addition, when we talk about the re-training strategy

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
necessary for organizational development,

07:10.000 --> 07:17.000
a very important value in this case is the problem of support

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
and reinforcement of the changes that are taking place,

07:20.000 --> 07:26.000
because all organizational development is a change in the relationship of people,

07:26.000 --> 07:30.000
it is a change in the interaction of people, it is a change in the functioning of people.

07:30.000 --> 07:35.000
There is no organizational development at all, there is no abstract organizational development.

07:35.000 --> 07:39.000
Organizational development is always an action, it is always a feeling,

07:39.000 --> 07:42.000
a relationship, a result, a function of those specific people,

07:42.000 --> 07:46.000
of those specific employees who are present in the company

07:46.000 --> 07:52.000
and who carry out, implement all the functioning that is carried out in the company.

07:52.000 --> 07:57.000
We will understand organizational development in this broad context,

07:57.000 --> 08:01.000
because the topic of our today's lesson is actually familiar,

08:01.000 --> 08:06.000
what kind of changes can occur,

08:06.000 --> 08:10.000
what kind of results of these changes can be present.

08:10.000 --> 08:17.000
And, accordingly, we want to familiarize ourselves with those various forms

08:17.000 --> 08:23.000
of organizational changes, organizational constructs that occur.

08:23.000 --> 08:32.000
We can make many arguments in favor of the necessity of organizational changes,

08:32.000 --> 08:40.000
but I think it is enough to refer to those people who are undisputed authorities

08:40.000 --> 08:45.000
in modern concept management, in modern commerce, in modern business.

08:45.000 --> 08:53.000
For example, Porter noted that competitors will immediately and necessarily introduce any company

08:53.000 --> 08:57.000
that will stop improving and introducing innovations.

08:57.000 --> 09:02.000
And there is only one way to maintain the achieved competitive advantages.

09:02.000 --> 09:08.000
They must be constantly improved and move in the direction of more complex forms.

09:09.000 --> 09:17.000
Porter means the obvious fact that not only small companies, not only newly emerging companies,

09:17.000 --> 09:23.000
but also monsters, brands that exist on the market, must also constantly change,

09:23.000 --> 09:29.000
because no matter what sector of the market you capture, no matter what part of the market you have,

09:29.000 --> 09:35.000
in any case, the successes and results achieved once will not be constant.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.000
There are competitors who claim the same market share.

09:39.000 --> 09:43.000
There are new companies that introduce new products.

09:43.000 --> 09:47.000
There is a struggle for the consumer, a struggle for demand,

09:47.000 --> 09:52.000
there are all kinds of concepts related to the offer of any goods and services.

09:52.000 --> 09:56.000
And there is a constant movement, constant change,

09:56.000 --> 10:04.000
which in no case allows for any constant and unchanging forms.

10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
And if we want to conform to the realities that exist on the market,

10:07.000 --> 10:10.000
we must constantly respond to these requests.

10:10.000 --> 10:15.000
There must be a constant feedback between the requests that occur

10:15.000 --> 10:17.000
and the proposals that we as a company issue,

10:17.000 --> 10:21.000
regardless of the existing merits, regardless of the past merits,

10:21.000 --> 10:25.000
regardless of the plans that we build for the future,

10:25.000 --> 10:28.000
regardless of the funds that are being invested.

10:29.000 --> 10:34.000
However, the process of organizational changes is a rather complex process,

10:34.000 --> 10:40.000
when it is quite difficult to predict the final result.

10:40.000 --> 10:49.000
Let's look at three facts that are the generalization of events on the market,

10:49.000 --> 10:57.000
which show that the organizational development of the companies is changing,

10:57.000 --> 11:02.000
and that the output efficiency is very low,

11:02.000 --> 11:08.000
in the sense that many things are changing, but not all of them are achieving the desired result.

11:08.000 --> 11:15.000
As the studies conducted in the last decades of the last century have shown,

11:15.000 --> 11:22.000
only a quarter of the projects on changing business processes were successful.

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
75% of the projects, three quarters,

11:24.000 --> 11:31.000
which included funds, which involved time and effort,

11:31.000 --> 11:34.000
did not lead not only to desired results,

11:34.000 --> 11:42.000
but to significant deterioration in the companies where they were invested,

11:42.000 --> 11:52.000
and three quarters of the companies were not able to achieve and even return the results that they had.

11:52.000 --> 11:54.000
Change is always a risk.

11:54.000 --> 11:59.000
It is a risk that either you achieve the result,

11:59.000 --> 12:01.000
get economic profit,

12:01.000 --> 12:06.000
or you will not lose what you had,

12:07.000 --> 12:09.000
the invested funds will not be recovered,

12:09.000 --> 12:17.000
and you will have to look for other ways and other opportunities for economic growth and economic development,

12:17.000 --> 12:19.000
which are still necessary to be carried out.

12:19.000 --> 12:25.000
Another figure indicates that usually companies,

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
as they grow,

12:27.000 --> 12:32.000
which are present and occupy a certain segment of the market,

12:33.000 --> 12:38.000
tend to merge to increase their share of influence,

12:38.000 --> 12:40.000
to increase their presence,

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
to increase their segment of the market,

12:42.000 --> 12:46.000
or more successful, larger companies,

12:46.000 --> 12:50.000
which control larger areas of the market,

12:50.000 --> 12:57.000
want to swallow smaller companies in order to get their resources,

12:57.000 --> 12:59.000
their achievements, their results,

12:59.000 --> 13:04.000
and in the end get the desired result.

13:04.000 --> 13:11.000
It turns out that despite the fact that a large number of mergers and acquisitions are carried out annually,

13:11.000 --> 13:15.000
only 25%, again, the same quarter,

13:15.000 --> 13:22.000
will be successful in terms of the fact that only the costs of these mergers and acquisitions are paid.

13:23.000 --> 13:32.000
Mergers and acquisitions are a process that requires significant time, financial, tax, customs efforts,

13:32.000 --> 13:36.000
and all these processes are costly.

13:36.000 --> 13:40.000
Only 25% of these costs are actually paid.

13:40.000 --> 13:43.000
Again, the same three quarters of mergers and acquisitions,

13:43.000 --> 13:48.000
at best, do not lead to the desired results,

13:48.000 --> 13:54.000
but to the growth of certain economic indicators for which these mergers and acquisitions were carried out.

13:54.000 --> 13:58.000
Again, I would like to emphasize that we are talking about a civilized business,

13:58.000 --> 14:02.000
which is mainly held in the West,

14:02.000 --> 14:05.000
or the civilized conditions of business in Russia,

14:05.000 --> 14:11.000
and in this case we are talking about economic indicators of mergers and acquisitions,

14:11.000 --> 14:16.000
without any other specific factors of this impact.

14:16.000 --> 14:25.000
The next example I would like to give is related to the widespread introduction of information technologies

14:25.000 --> 14:28.000
and information systems at large enterprises.

14:28.000 --> 14:35.000
Today, a great importance, as you all know, is the use of computer technology,

14:35.000 --> 14:38.000
computer processing, computer control,

14:38.000 --> 14:43.000
and the automation of business processes that are carried out at enterprises.

14:44.000 --> 14:49.000
Moreover, since these processes are quite costly,

14:49.000 --> 14:54.000
only large organizations, large companies, large companies

14:54.000 --> 15:01.000
are able to allocate free funds to carry out any other information interventions.

15:01.000 --> 15:07.000
So, despite the fact that the number of funds that are constantly invested

15:08.000 --> 15:12.000
in the process of introducing information technologies,

15:12.000 --> 15:16.000
in the process of automated production management,

15:16.000 --> 15:22.000
only 9%, even less than a quarter, of these funds are being spent.

15:22.000 --> 15:27.000
Less than a tenth of the funds, less than a tenth of the projects,

15:27.000 --> 15:33.000
of the entire huge number of projects for the introduction of information systems and technologies, are being spent.

15:34.000 --> 15:39.000
That is, at least justify the funds that are invested in them.

15:39.000 --> 15:42.000
And in this regard, another problem arises.

15:42.000 --> 15:45.000
The funds are already very often being invested,

15:45.000 --> 15:51.000
however, the managers see that the investment of these funds does not give the desired return,

15:51.000 --> 15:58.000
there is disappointment, and 31%, that is, a third of all these projects,

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
are simply not fully satisfied.

16:00.000 --> 16:04.000
The funds were invested, the expectations were high,

16:04.000 --> 16:12.000
the organizational structures, organizational management systems were planned,

16:12.000 --> 16:18.000
and the problem of introducing information systems is not a problem of a day, a week, a month,

16:18.000 --> 16:21.000
it is a problem that can last a quarter, six months, a year.

16:21.000 --> 16:27.000
And now, after a long period of time, the management is convinced

16:27.000 --> 16:30.000
that the desired result is not what has not been achieved,

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
but there are deteriorations in the work,

16:32.000 --> 16:38.000
there are changes in those or other problems that exist in the company,

16:38.000 --> 16:43.000
and the management refuses to continue the introduction of information technologies

16:43.000 --> 16:46.000
and strives to return to what was before.

16:46.000 --> 16:49.000
This is not always possible, as we have already said,

16:49.000 --> 16:54.000
because changes have the quality that if they have started,

16:54.000 --> 16:58.000
they already destroy the existing structure,

16:58.000 --> 17:03.000
they change those or other processes that occur in the organization,

17:03.000 --> 17:09.000
and, in the end, we all work with living people,

17:09.000 --> 17:14.000
and it is impossible to make a click, for example, on a project, on a photo shoot,

17:14.000 --> 17:17.000
and return everything to the initial conditions,

17:17.000 --> 17:21.000
in order to start from the beginning as if nothing had happened.

17:22.000 --> 17:27.000
If we look at the actual results, at the economic indicators,

17:27.000 --> 17:35.000
it turns out that a large number of organizational changes,

17:35.000 --> 17:41.000
a large number of organizational development results are not fully achieved,

17:41.000 --> 17:47.000
and, at best, a quarter of these projects lead to some result.

17:47.000 --> 17:57.000
But this quarter leads to significant changes, significant shifts in the market,

17:57.000 --> 18:03.000
and in this regard, those companies that brought the corresponding changes to the end,

18:03.000 --> 18:11.000
those companies that made up the future plan of further development,

18:12.000 --> 18:17.000
the plan of these changes, which introduced both strategic and tactical changes,

18:17.000 --> 18:22.000
they achieve significant results and become leaders,

18:22.000 --> 18:25.000
become leaders again for a certain time.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
This is the leadership that requires constant support,

18:28.000 --> 18:33.000
this is the leadership that requires constant investment of funds,

18:33.000 --> 18:37.000
constant control of the availability of feedback,

18:37.000 --> 18:44.000
and this is the leadership that is supported only by reacting to those changes,

18:44.000 --> 18:49.000
those requests, those needs that are presented to the company both from the market

18:49.000 --> 18:56.000
and based on those internal reasons for the development, existence and functioning of the company.

18:57.000 --> 19:03.000
The next question that we would like to consider is what is good.

19:03.000 --> 19:10.000
Changes are necessary, changes are being made, changes require certain costs,

19:10.000 --> 19:14.000
changes do not always lead to the desired result,

19:14.000 --> 19:21.000
but still, what are the successful models of changes,

19:21.000 --> 19:26.000
or what models describe the process of organizational change and development,

19:26.000 --> 19:39.000
and what models can serve as the basis on which we can build the process of change in each particular company.

19:40.000 --> 19:44.000
It should be said right away that there are a lot of these models.

19:44.000 --> 19:51.000
These models depend on what the company produces, on the services that it provides.

19:52.000 --> 19:58.000
These models depend on different aspects of business,

19:58.000 --> 20:05.000
these models are different in different industries, in different elements of business,

20:05.000 --> 20:14.000
but the main goal, the main task of these models is to highlight the main elements

20:14.000 --> 20:19.000
that should be paid attention to in order to build a certain strategy,

20:19.000 --> 20:24.000
in order to create a strategic plan of development.

20:25.000 --> 20:33.000
Organizational change models are closely related to the growth models, to the organizational change models.

20:34.000 --> 20:40.000
We will consider, for example, the model proposed by Leon Danko,

20:41.000 --> 20:49.000
and this model shows the connection between the process of business growth and time

20:49.000 --> 20:53.000
that has passed since the moment of the company's emergence and development.

20:54.000 --> 20:58.000
This model highlights five main periods,

20:58.000 --> 21:04.000
and in each of these periods there are certain difficulties,

21:04.000 --> 21:08.000
certain crisis points that need to be overcome,

21:09.000 --> 21:20.000
because these are the critical moments, critical elements that arise in the development of each organization.

21:22.000 --> 21:26.000
As for the original element of the model,

21:26.000 --> 21:29.000
when the company is just emerging,

21:29.000 --> 21:35.000
when the company begins to fight for the conquest of certain markets,

21:35.000 --> 21:38.000
then this is a period of so-called hard work.

21:39.000 --> 21:45.000
We really put in effort, we establish contacts, we establish connections,

21:45.000 --> 21:48.000
we are persistently fighting for consumers,

21:48.000 --> 21:51.000
because the company does not usually emerge in the open,

21:51.000 --> 21:54.000
it emerges already with the presence of other companies,

21:54.000 --> 21:57.000
and accordingly it needs to find its niche,

21:57.000 --> 22:00.000
find its niche in that market, in that business that exists.

22:00.000 --> 22:05.000
This is really hard work, it requires a regular working day,

22:05.000 --> 22:07.000
it requires new unexpected solutions,

22:07.000 --> 22:14.000
it requires a very fast response to the requests that occur,

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
it requires a very fast feedback.

22:17.000 --> 22:22.000
As for the results of this hard work, they are unpredictable again.

22:23.000 --> 22:27.000
Most companies can't withstand such a load,

22:27.000 --> 22:29.000
they may not have enough funds,

22:29.000 --> 22:32.000
they may have internal conflicts and contradictions,

22:32.000 --> 22:34.000
they may have problems with their founders,

22:35.000 --> 22:44.000
and accordingly they are less successful and do not stand out,

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
not only as a leader, but they stand out,

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
at least in the middle of the market,

22:48.000 --> 22:51.000
they leave the market, they re-profile,

22:51.000 --> 22:53.000
disintegrate, absorb, merge,

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
do something else,

22:56.000 --> 23:02.000
but in fact these are the companies that could not withstand the competition

23:02.000 --> 23:10.000
and were forced to re-profile their activities or stop their existence.

23:11.000 --> 23:13.000
This is the majority of companies.

23:13.000 --> 23:15.000
According to the research,

23:15.000 --> 23:24.000
on average, about 85-90% of newly formed companies are unsuccessful.

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
But again, if this company arises,

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
of course, this company is small at first,

23:29.000 --> 23:33.000
and accordingly, it is like a small business,

23:33.000 --> 23:35.000
it has such a search activity,

23:35.000 --> 23:37.000
where can I get involved,

23:37.000 --> 23:40.000
where can I enter the already divided,

23:40.000 --> 23:43.000
already formed economic market.

23:43.000 --> 23:49.000
And only 10% or a little more of newly formed companies

23:50.000 --> 23:52.000
find their place under the sun,

23:52.000 --> 23:57.000
and conquer part of the market,

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
their economic segment,

23:59.000 --> 24:03.000
and begin to develop further.

24:04.000 --> 24:07.000
This is the next stage of the fall,

24:07.000 --> 24:09.000
this is the stage of creating myths,

24:09.000 --> 24:12.000
creating myths about how we started,

24:12.000 --> 24:14.000
how it all was, what we achieved,

24:14.000 --> 24:16.000
thanks to what we did it.

24:16.000 --> 24:19.000
This is the period of the creation of corporate culture of the company,

24:19.000 --> 24:21.000
corporate history of the company.

24:21.000 --> 24:25.000
This is the period of creating corporate norms,

24:25.000 --> 24:28.000
corporate regulations, corporate ethics.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.000
And as for this period,

24:31.000 --> 24:33.000
this is really a period of mythologization,

24:33.000 --> 24:41.000
when we try to forget about those failures that inevitably occurred,

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
when we try to forget about those losses that occurred,

24:44.000 --> 24:48.000
and like any ordinary living person,

24:48.000 --> 24:53.000
we try to remember only positive things,

24:53.000 --> 25:04.000
that were certain steps that led us from zero to the success that we have now achieved.

25:04.000 --> 25:10.000
In principle, all the big companies that exist today

25:10.000 --> 25:14.000
are companies that have been thrown around by various kinds of myths.

25:14.000 --> 25:18.000
The same brands that are present on the market,

25:18.000 --> 25:25.000
it is always a kind of a combination of myths related to one or another brand.

